===Etymology 2===
{{zh-forms|s=壮|alt=獞-obsolete,僮-obsolete}}
First written as {{m|zh|獞}} (composed of {{m|zh|犭}}, the “beast” radical, and {{m|zh|童}}, “servant”). Following the foundation of the {{w|People’s Republic of China}}, it was written as {{m|zh|僮}} (with {{m|zh|亻}}, the “person” radical). Due to the derogatory connotations of the previous characters, it was officially amended to {{zh-l|壯|strong; robust}} in 1965.

